Minute Entry for proceedings held before Chief Magistrate Judge Justo Arenas :Detention Hearing as to Dennis Muniz-Tirado held on 8/24/2007. AUSA Scott Anderson and defense counsel Johnny Rivera were present. The Government requested detention without bail. Defense counsel was heard by proffer. The Court set bond as to Dennis Muniz-Tirado (1) in the amount of $100,000 cash or secured to be posted within 10 working days. The Government had no objection to the 10 days. The Court ordered defendant to be released today on a $100,000 unsecured bond. In ten (10) days, the unsecured bond will be secured. Standard release conditions imposed. Any other detailed release condition will be announced by Probation Office, Pretrial Division. (Court Reporter FTR/bg, CD: Brenda Gonzalez, CI: Janis Palma, PO: Dana Rodriguez) (br) (Entered: 08/28/2007)

Minute Entry for proceedings held before Chief Magistrate Judge Justo Arenas :Detention Hearing as to Anthony Dominguez-Colon held on 8/27/2007. AUSA Scott Anderson and defense counsel Carlos Rodriguez were present. The Government was heard by proffer as to defendant's role and/or participation and strongly requested detention without bail pending trial. Defense counsel was also heard by proffer, but requested a bond lower than the one recommended in the pretrial report. After hearing the parties, the Court set bond as to Anthony Dominguez-Colon (3) in the amount of $100,000 cash or secured by real estate. Standard release conditions is imposed. Any other detailed or special release condition(s), will be conferred with the Probation Office, Pretrial Division.(Court Reporter FTR/bg, CD: Brenda Gonzalez, CI: Janis Palma, PO: Dana Rodriguez) (br, ) (Entered: 08/28/2007)

ORDER. Urgent motion requesting witness appearance certification, docket 457 is denied. The Court can not provide a certificate as to compliance since there is no procedures for the Court to verify who accompanied the defendant Ruperto Torres (5)on each date. Agent Vazquez certainly was not a witness in this case, if she had would not have been allowed to remain in the courtroom during the proceedings. In addition, Agent Vazquez was never placed under the rules of the Court. The Court can only state that she was present during most if not the whole trial proceedings. Therefore, certification of appearances requested is denied. IT IS SO ORDERED. Signed by Judge Daniel R. Dominguez on 02/17/2009. (om) (Entered: 02/17/2009)

ORDER denying 455 Motion under Rule 29 as to Luis Ruperto-Torres (5). As to the alternate Request for Bail (Docket 455) as to Luis Ruperto Torres see order issued on this same date as to Docket 464. The only new matter is as to the Henriquez arrest alleging that the victim identified Luis Ruperto Torres being in another car at the time of arrest. But defendant forgets that defendant himself admitted that in order to arrest Henriquez we came all the way up to here. We can not be interpreted referring to other persons excluding Luis Ruperto Torres as the words came from him. (See Ex. 11, p. 44-46). Further, the facts in a conspiracy are interpreted in the light most favorable to the verdict as opposed to the light most favorable to the defendant. See United States v. Wihbey, 75 F.3d 761, 774 (1st Cir. 1996) citing United States v. David, 940 F.2d 722 (1st Cir. 1991) cert. denied 502 U.S. 989 (1991). As to the Rule 29 request, the motion is under advisement pending argument on March 9, 2009 at 2:00 p.m. IT IS SO ORDERED. Signed by Judge Daniel R. Dominguez on 2-23-09. (nild) (Entered: 02/23/2009)

The Court has detected structural errors and the repeating of citations which should have been abbreviated, after the first citation. Said case had been cited by the Court at the oral argument as to the renewed Rule 29 motion (decision still pending). There are no new matters contained in the Second Amended Order, other than the reference of the case of United States v. Upton, 559 F.3d at 13. The Clerk of the Court shall notify the parties and shall notify the Appeals Court  Clerk of the instant Second Amended Order Denying Bail. IT IS SO ORDERED. Signed by Judge Daniel R.
